description.narrative:
The Finnish Development Aid Programme in Mozambique in 2013 is 21 783 000 euros and 24 393 000 euros in 2014. The Support to Mozambique consists of general budget support education sector (FASE) the Administrative Court (TA) and Institute for Social Studie
s (IESE) supports and the Support to Rural development in Zambezia Province (PROEDEZA II) Science Technology and Innovation (STIFIMO) and forest sector's institutional cooperation (Forecas) projects. Planning of NGO support to the agricultural sector (ADPP
) is under process including the finalilzation of the programme document. In 2014 the plannings of good governance early childhoos and taxation projects will be under process.
